 Hooker."},"tags":["hooker_talcott_descent","civil_war"],"sources":[{"label":"FindAGrave — Roger A Francis"}],"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I00194","date_month":1,"date_day":1,"location_state":"New York","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1885,"children_ids":[]}],"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Roger","middle_name":"A","last_name":"Francis","married_names":[],"display_name":"Roger A Francis","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1777740226/rogerfrancis_m4ru0q.jpg"},"residence":{"city":"Bridgehampton","county":"Suffolk","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[{"war":"American Civil War","war_id":"WAR006","rank":"Captain","rank_end":"Captain","rank_year_start":1862,"unit":"81st New York State Volunteer Infantry Regiment (Second Oswego Regiment, after consolidation with Mohawk Rifle Regiment)","notes":"Captain in the 81st New York State Volunteer Infantry Regiment, known as the Second Oswego Regiment after its February 10, 1862 consolidation with the Mohawk Rifle Regiment. The regiment left the barracks at Albany NY for the seat of war on February 21, 1862. The 81st NY served through the Peninsula Campaign and the Siege of Petersburg. Specific battles in which Capt. Francis fought are not yet documented at the individual level."}],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM115","plot_notes":"Bridgehampton Cemetery, Bridgehampton, Suffolk County NY. FindAGrave confirms."},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"Civil War captain; mother died age 33","body":"Roger A. Francis served as a Civil War captain; his Bridgehampton merchant career and Stamford Connecticut residence followed his service. Born in May 1826 at 